results.headline: China Protests U.S. Law Supporting Hong Kong but Signals Hope for Trade Deal
results.paragraph: BEIJING—China held off from retaliating against the U.S. after President Trump signed a bill supporting Hong Kong’s anti-Beijing protesters, as both sides remained confident they can sign a partial trade deal in the coming weeks, officials in the U.S. and China said.

results.headline: India's economy seen growing at 4.7% in Sept qtr
results.paragraph: India's economy probably expanded at its weakest pace in more than six years in the quarter to September, a Reuters poll showed, as consumer demand and private investment weakened further and a global slowdown hit exports.

results.headline: Capitalism is in crisis. And we cannot get out of it by carrying on as before

How the Quantum Tech Race Puts the World's Data at Risk
results.paragraph: The technology one-upmanship between the United States and China is fast becoming the new space race. There's been a lot of talk in the press about the competition to reach 5G, but little traction outside of the tech community about something more momentous: the dangers of computing in a post-quantum world.
